Polish Stocks: BRE Bank, Comp, Handlowy, KGHM, Lotos, Orlen

-- B y   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i
-- 
2011-05-23T15:52:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/polish-stocks-comp-handlowy-kghm-lotos-orlen-pekao-shares.html
Poland ’s WIG20 Index declined 12.73,
or 0.5 percent, to 2,816.70 at the 5:30 p.m. close in Warsaw,
falling to the lowest level in almost a week.  The following are among the most active stocks on the
 Warsaw Stock Exchange  today. Stock symbols follow company names.  BRE Bank SA (BRE)  , a unit of Commerzbank AG, declined 4
zloty, or 1.2 percent, to 336 zloty. Bank Handlowy SA (BHW PW),
controlled by Citigroup Inc., lost 1.65 zloty, or 1.7 percent,
to 95.7 zloty.  Banking shares fell across  Europe  on concern the region’s
sovereign debt crisis is deepening.  Comp SA (CMP)   sank 4 zloty, or 4.8 percent, to 80 zloty,
falling the most since October as the software maker was cut to
“hold” from “buy” at ING Groep NV.  KGHM Polska Miedz SA (KGH)  , Poland’s sole copper
producer, retreated 1.9 zloty, or 1.1 percent, to 179.7 zloty,
closing at the lowest level in almost a week. Copper fell as
manufacturing slowed in  China , the world’s largest buyer of
industrial metals.  PKN Orlen SA (PKN PW), Poland’s biggest oil company, lost
0.35 zloty, or 0.7 percent, to 51.1 zloty.  Grupa Lotos SA (LTS)  , the second-largest refiner, fell 0.8 zloty, or 1.7 percent,
to 45.2 zloty. Crude oil dropped on concern Europe’s sovereign
debt crisis will spread, slowing economic growth and reducing
fuel demand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pawel Kozlowski in Warsaw 
